de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.temporal

Class TemporalFusion

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.temporal.TemporalFusion

  • public class TemporalFusion
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is responsible for fusing temporal metadata. Therefore the metadata information corresponding to every URI are added to the metadata set by calling add(int, ParsedMetadata). After all metadata information is added the fuse(HashMap) is called. It fulfills the OPTICS OF algorithm to generate a clustering. At the end the createTemporalProperty(ClusteringResult, HashMap) method builds the scopeResource which contains the fused temporal metadata information to add them to the metadataModel later.
    Since:
    24.02.2014
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:

      • add

        public void add(int metadataIndex,
       ParsedMetadata singleMetadata)
        This method builds a TemporalClusteringObject with metadata index and the timestamp parsed by getTemporalTimestamp(ParsedMetadata) method. Afterwards it adds the newly created object to the temporalMetadata set.
        Parameters:
        metadataIndex - - an int value which represents the metadata index of the also given ParsedMetadata object.
        singleMetadata - - a ParsedMetadata object which contains the timestamp.

      • getTemporalTimestamp

        private long getTemporalTimestamp(ParsedMetadata singleMetadata)
        This method returns the timestamp of a given ParsedMetadata object as a long value or -1, in case the object has no timestamp metadata. If a timestamp is valid, the setBoundaries(long) method is called to set the minTimestamp and/or maxTimestamp as appropriate.
        Parameters:
        singleMetadata - - a ParsedMetadata object.
        Returns:
        a long value which represents the timestamp of the given ParsedMetadata object.

      • setBoundaries

        private void setBoundaries(long timestamp)
        This method checks whether the given timestamp is one of the boundaries. If it is smaller then the minTimestamp it becomes the new minTimestamp. Same for the maxTimestamp. Notice that this method is only called if a real timestamp exists, so -1 is never a boundary.
        Parameters:
        timestamp - - a long value which represents the timestamp in milliseconds.

      • fuse

        public void fuse(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,ParsedMetadata> metadataMap)
        This method fuses the temporal properties of all chosen metadata information and calls the createTemporalProperty(ClusteringResult, HashMap) method to append a RDF representation to the scopeResource. At the beginning the neighborhoodRadius and the minNeighbors are calculated. They are needed for the TemporalClusterDetector which performs the OPTICS OF algorithm. The calling of TemporalClusterDetector.detectClusters(TreeSet) does the clustering and the ClusteringResult is passed to the createTemporalProperty(ClusteringResult, HashMap) method finally.
        Parameters:
        metadataMap - - a HashMap which matches a metadata index to it's corresponding ParsedMetadata object.

      • calculateNeighborhoodRadius

        private double calculateNeighborhoodRadius()
        This method is responsible for calculating the neighborhood radius. This value represents the distance in which the OPTICS-OF algorithm searches for neighbors later.
        Returns:
        the neighborhood radius - a double value.

      • calculateMinNeighbors

        private int calculateMinNeighbors()
        This method returns the minimal amount of neighbors to identify a cluster according to the count of elements the OPTICS algorithm is performed with.
        Returns:
        a int value.

      • createTemporalProperty

        private void createTemporalProperty(ClusteringResult clusteringResult,
                          java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,ParsedMetadata> metadataMap)
        This method is responsible for adding the temporal metadata information to the temporal scope property. Therefore it iterates over the noMetadata, outliers and clusters lists and calls the specific methods to add the metadata to the scopeResource.
        Parameters:
        clusteringResult - - the ClusteringResult object created by the OPTICS OF algorithm containing the lists of noMetadata, outliers and clusters.
        metadataMap - - a HashMap which matches the metadata index to a corresponding ParsedMetadata object.

                                    java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,ParsedMetadata> metadataMap)
        This method transforms the metadata indices given by the ClusteringResult object to the actual URIs. The list is used to call the MatchingHelper.groupNoMetadataUris(java.util.List) to obtain the returned NoMetadataObject.

        clusteringResult - - the ClusteringResult object created by the OPTICS OF algorithm containing the lists of noMetadata, outliers and clusters.

        a NoMetadataObject.

      • addClusterProperty

        private void addClusterProperty(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> clusterIndices,
                      java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,ParsedMetadata> metadataMap,
                      int clusterNumber)
        This method adds the cluster properties to the scopeResource. First of all it generates the minimum and maximum date of a cluster by iteration all metadata indices and calling updateClusterMinTimestamp(String, TemporalScope) respectivly updateClusterMaxTimestamp(String, TemporalScope). Afterwards a new Resource object with maximum and minimum dates is created and added to the scopeResource.
        Parameters:
        clusterIndices - - an ArrayList of int values which represent all metadata indices of objects in the current cluster.
        metadataMap - - a HashMap which matches a metadata index to it's corresponding ParsedMetadata object.
        clusterNumber - - an int value which represents the number of the current cluster.

      • updateClusterMinTimestamp

        private java.lang.String updateClusterMinTimestamp(java.lang.String clusterMinDate,
                                         TemporalScope temporalScope)
        This method updates the clusterMinTimestamp. If the timestamp of the given TemporalScope object is smaller than the clusterMinTimestamp the new minimum is set and the timestamp is returned as a String value. Otherwise the minimum String stays the same.
        Parameters:
        clusterMinDate - - a String value which represents the current minimum date.
        temporalScope - - the current TemporalScope object.
        Returns:
        a String value which represents the updated minimum date.
